The paper deals with the problem of finding the closest lattice point in a distributed network setting, which involves communication and information theory (cs.IT). The study of communication cost and error probability also falls under distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The use of algorithms and computational methods to solve the problem relates to numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the importance of proper basis selection and reduction in dimensions suggests a possible connection to signal processing and information retrieval (cs.SI).
